<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/33561398-stefania-lazar"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1406896333i/33561398._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/33561398-stefania-lazar">Stefania Lazar</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">All three novels forming the American Trilogy are stand-alones. They are only considered a trilogy because they have a similar setting (New England/Ne<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">All three novels forming the American Trilogy are stand-alones. They are only considered a trilogy because they have a similar setting (New England/New Jersey in the second half of the 20th century) and similar social themes.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
